1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:08,000
AI agents are shipping to production faster than any prior software category.

2
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Every team I've worked with ships them the same way — hope it works, pray it scales, debug post-incident.

3
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:23,000
What's missing is the testing discipline traditional software earned over decades.

4
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:30,000
This is AgentClinic. Five golden traces, each published natively into UiPath Test Cloud.

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:40,000
Click into the failed log. Look at the reason. This is the difference.

6
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:50,000
Not "agent looks bad" — but the exact finding ID, severity, confidence, and trace event IDs that drove the verdict.

7
00:00:50,000 --> 00:01:00,000
A reviewer can jump from this dialog straight to events evt_0002 through evt_0004 in the source trace.

8
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:07,000
The chain is unbroken. Every claim points at evidence.

9
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:18,000
Why does this work? Because the judge and the coach are different things.

10
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:28,000
The judge is a deterministic Python rule engine — no LLM, source-controlled rules, same verdict every time.

11
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:38,000
The coach uses an LLM, but is bounded by a validator that blocks judge-reserved phrases.

12
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:44,000
The coach translates findings into remediation. It never judges. Coach, not surveillance.

13
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:55,000
Seven detectors. All deterministic, all source-controlled.

14
00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:05,000
Hard hat loop catches blind retries with the state hash unchanged.

15
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:13,000
Every finding produced must include an evidence span — specific trace event IDs as the contract requires.

16
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Section five — information gaps. When data is missing, the report admits what it cannot judge.

17
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:25,000
No guessing. No hallucination. That iron rule is what makes a clinic different from a courtroom.

18
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:35,000
Run it locally first. The CLI normalizes the trace, runs the seven detectors, scores L0 to L3.

19
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:50,000
Then drives the full Test Manager API chain — project, test case, test set, execution, case log, override, attachment.

20
00:02:50,000 --> 00:03:00,000
Every step real, every ID a live resource. publish_error null, result_override_error null. Reproducible.

21
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Same agent, this time triggered from Automation Cloud.

22
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:20,000
The Orchestrator process invokes the Coded Agent — same pipeline, credentials from env vars on the process.

23
00:03:20,000 --> 00:03:30,000
The job completes. Back in Test Manager, a new execution appears.

24
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Open the failed log, open the override dialog — and there it is.

25
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:50,000
The same multi-line evidence-bound reason. Same finding ID. Same trace event IDs.

26
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:55,000
Cloud runtime writes the same audit record as local runtime, every time.

27
00:03:55,000 --> 00:04:05,000
Four roles, no overlap. Judge deterministic — LLM cannot revise the verdict.

28
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:13,000
Coach rides UiPath's AgentHub LLM Gateway, every call inside the AI Trust Layer.

29
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:20,000
No direct LLM provider API key. Test Cloud is the system of record. Orchestrator ties it all together.

30
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:30,000
Six native UiPath components — Track 3 framing: quality as a continuous, governed capability.

31
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Repository public, MIT licensed. CI green across trace goldens, budget goldens, and Coded Agent build.

32
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:45,000
Every line written by Claude Code over eleven days — twenty-plus commits, every one in the log.

33
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:50,000
Drop a trace in, get an audit trail. AgentClinic — coach, not surveillance. Thank you.
